reviews.text: Food's pretty good, and prices are reasonable given the competition in the area. Keep in mind if you're a Westerner: service works differently in China, you'll need to hail the waitstaff to your table, they won't just check in constantly like in Europe/the States. Try the fried rice and anchovies!

A Thai restaurant with Outdoor seat in the central of TST, waiter is very friendly, I order one cocktail and told them it taste too sweet, they give me one extra shot directly 🤣 food also taste good, but some of our friends doesn’t feel well at the next day after eating the raw shrimp. But I will come here next time

We walked past and decided to eat at Nara Thai Restaurant in Hong Kong.  The staff refused to acknowledge us, in the end we got our own menus, had to ask for drinks 3 times.  Tables walking in after us got service before us.  Not sure if this was because we were westerners or not.  It's a pity as mist reviews have been good.
Thai food is amazing. Normally good offer on Beers too. Highly recommended
My all time favorite food is Thai and Tom yum especially, they did not disappoint, would definitely recommend this place if you're looking craving for some authentic Thai food !
